investments, at cost
as of september30, 2002 and 2001, the
company held $14million and $92million,
respectively, of securities classified as available-for-sale. as
of september30, 2002 and september30, 2001, the
company also held $148million and $472million,
respectively, of non-public cost method investments. realized
gains and losses are determined principally on an average cost
basis. in 2002, 2001 and 2000, the company recognized
$239million, $87million and $41million,
respectively, in net gains on sales of securities. included in
fiscal 2002 is a $216million gain on the sale of the
remaining shares of knight ridder stock that the company had
received in connection with the disposition of certain
publishing operations that had been acquired in connection with
the acquisition of abc.
in addition, in 2002 and 2001, the company
