repurchased $194million of the notes prior to the stated
maturity date. the abc family notes were redeemable by abc
family starting november1, 2002 and semi-annually
thereafter. abc family exercised its right to redeem the notes
and, accordingly, all of the outstanding abc family notes were
redeemed on november1, 2002 at a price of 104.625% for the
senior notes and 105.125% of the principal amount for the senior
discount notes. the redemption did not have a material impact on
the company. as of september30, 2002, the abc family notes
were classified as current.
